         <div type="translation" resp="part:nabo">
             <div type="textpart" n="A"><head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
                    <p>The charter belongs to the illustrious king Narendra who chastised his enemies, who was the son of Śarabha who conquered the earth with the blade of his sword.</p></div>
             <div type="textpart" n="B"><head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
                    <p n="1v1-1v3">Success! Hail! From Śarabhapura, the illustrious Mahārāja Narendra informs the landholders, beginning with the Brahmins, settled in <supplied reason="subaudible">the village of</supplied> Sarkarāpadraka situated in the Nandapura <foreign>bhoga</foreign>:</p>
                    <p n="1v4-2r5">This village has been granted by Rāhudeva for the increase of his own <supplied reason="explanation">religious</supplied> merit to the Brahmin Svāmippa, belonging to the Ātreya <foreign>gotra</foreign> and to the Vājasaneya <supplied reason="subaudible">school</supplied>, by means of a copperplate charter; and <supplied reason="subaudible">the grant</supplied> is thus also confirmed by me, <supplied reason="subaudible">making it</supplied> not to be entered by irregular or regular troops. Therefore, you should render taxes consisting of the <supplied reason="subaudible">proper</supplied> shares of produce, gold, et cetera at the proper time.</p>
                    <p n="2r5-2v4">And he <supplied reason="explanation">Narendra</supplied> instructs the future rulers: The protection of <supplied reason="subaudible">the grant of</supplied> this village should be taken care of by you, well-discerning that: Prosperity derives from protecting a grant made previously, and sin derives from confiscating <supplied reason="subaudible">such a grant</supplied>. In this respect, they quote two stanzas sung by Vyāsa:</p>
                    <p n="2v4-3r1" rend="stanza">O Yudhiṣṭhira, zealously protect what was previously given to Brahmins! O best of kings, protection is superior to giving!</p>
                    <p n="3r2-3r4" rend="stanza">A giver of land dwells in heaven for sixty thousand years; he who confiscates it or allows <supplied reason="subaudible">another to confiscate it</supplied> will dwell for the same period in hell!</p>
                    <p n="3r4-3r5"><supplied reason="subaudible">The copperplate charter</supplied> has been engraved by Srīdatta on the tenth day of the month of Mārgaśiras of the prosperous third year <supplied reason="subaudible">of Narendra’s reign</supplied>.</p></div></div>
